headline: Costco Rotisserie Chicken Lawsuit And What It Could Mean For Valuation
summary: A nationwide class-action lawsuit claims Costco falsely markets its Kirkland Signature Seasoned Rotisserie Chicken as having "no preservatives." Filings allege the product contains ingredients that can function as preservatives, raising questions about accuracy in food labeling. The case targets Costco Wholesale, listed as NasdaqGS:COST, and focuses on consumer expectations around label transparency.
